                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d658">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.24/2–1346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in China</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-02-15T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >February 15, 1946—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>298. For General Marshall from Colonel Davis: Army indicates Yuan indebtedness
                    for calendar year 1945 will approximate Yuan $103 billion and for first half
                    1946 Yuan $10 billion. Navy estimates its Yuan indebtedness for 1946 to be
                    approximately Yuan $840 million and states it is unable to estimate 1946 debt
                    (Urtel 285, February 13). Treasury converting Yuan figures into US dollars but
                    reluctant to give out US dollar figure until approved by Secretary Vinson or Mr.
                    Harry White<note n="75" xml:id="d658fn75">Harry Dexter White, Assistant
                        Secretary of the Treasury.</note>—both of whom are out of city. Expect to
                    forward Treasury views early next week. Above figures exceedingly tentative and
                    further subject to minor exceptions which will be noted in succeeding cable.
                    Army 1945 figure does not take into account billeting and food supplied by
                    Chinese as reciprocal aid to War Area Service Command [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Corps</hi>]. [Davis.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
